# Claude Code prompt delivery (copy-paste)

When the user asks for prompts to send to Claude Code — including parallel streams, handoffs, "give me the prompt", "Stream A and B", or after Mode B setup — **deliver prompts as fenced code blocks only**, ready to copy in one click.

## Required format

### Single slice

One fenced block containing the **entire** prompt (use `═══` sections per [`.ai/tickets/CLAUDE_CODE_PROMPT.md`](.ai/tickets/CLAUDE_CODE_PROMPT.md)). Brief one-line intro above the block is OK; **do not** split the prompt across prose paragraphs.

### Parallel streams (e.g. two independent slices both on `main`)

**Exactly N code blocks for N streams** — typically **two**:

1. Short heading: `# Stream A — {slice id} {title}` + CWD one-liner (`repo root`, `main`)
2. **One complete fenced block** with the full prompt (everything Claude needs)
3. Short heading: `# Stream B — …`
4. **One complete fenced block** with the full prompt

Default is **main-only** (no `ticket/T-0xx` worktrees). Preflight bash may be a **third small block** at the end (optional) — never substitute it for the main prompt blocks.

## Forbidden

- Summarizing the prompt in prose instead of a copy-paste block
- "See handoff.md" as the only deliverable when user asked for the prompt
- One block with both streams concatenated without clear separation
- Partial prompts ("run these commands, then ask for part 2")
- Bullet lists that duplicate content **outside** the fenced block when user wanted the full prompt

## Source of truth

Build from: slice spec §Claude Code prompt, `.ai/artifacts/*_handoff.md`, `./scripts/ticket brief`. If `./scripts/ticket prompt` fails (no § in spec), **still** output the full handoff-derived block — do not tell user to run the script instead of pasting.

## Example shape (parallel)

```markdown
# Stream A — T-090.1.1 Map cartographic view

**CWD:** repo root (`main`)

```
{full prompt — PREFLIGHT, READ, PROBLEM, DO, DO NOT, VERIFY, RETURN}
```

# Stream B — T-068.11 Compiler loadout export

**CWD:** repo root (`main`)

```
{full prompt — PREFLIGHT, READ, PROBLEM, DO, DO NOT, VERIFY, RETURN}
```
```
